Package graph

Class Node

  • java.lang.Object
    • graph.Node
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Vertex
    public class Node
extends java.lang.Object
implements Vertex
    The Node class is an implementation of the Vertex. It provides the methods for the graphs whose implementation utilises adjacency lists. Each Node has a linked-list provided by java.util.LinkedList of objects of type Link, the class which implements the Edge interface.

    The assignment of the ID of a vertex is handled by the constructor of the class.

    See Also:
    Link

      • addEdge

        public boolean addEdge​(Vertex v,
                       int weight)
        Description copied from interface: Vertex
        Adds a new outward edge between this vertex and the other vertex passed as a parameter.

        As it is not allowed to have multiple outward edges pointing to same node, if an edge is found between this and another vertex by Vertex.containsEdge(...), that edge is not inserted and false is returned.

        Specified by:
        addEdge in interface Vertex
        Parameters:
        v - the vertex to which a outward edge is to be connected.
        weight - the weight to be assigned to the new edge.
        Returns:
        true if the insertion of the new edge is successful
